Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Cook and stir bacon in large skillet on medium heat 10 min. or until crisp. Remove bacon from skillet with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels. Discard all but 2 Tbsp. drippings from skillet. Add potatoes, mushrooms, peppers and onions to reserved drippings in skillet; cook 10 min. or until peppers and onions are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in VELVEETA. Spoon into 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray. Whisk eggs and sour cream in medium bowl until blended; stir in bacon. Pour over vegetable mixture. Bake 40 min. or until center is set and casserole is heated through.